      <entry xml:id="entry_mæskʼ_3" xml:lang="os-x-iron" abv:completeness="complete" n="3">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>mæskʼ</orth></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>кромка ткани</q>
            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>edge of fabric</q>
            </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>selvage</q>
            </abv:tr></sense></sense>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, из <w type="rec">mærz-k</w> с выпадением <c>r</c>, как в <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_baz"><w>baz</w>
            <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">из <w type="rec">barz</w></note>
            <gloss><q>подушка</q></gloss></ref>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/> из <w
            type="rec">tars</w>
          <gloss><q>страх</q></gloss> и др. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>marz</w>
            <gloss><q>предел</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>граница</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="got"><lang/>
            <w>marka</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
            <w>Mark</w>
            <gloss><q>граница</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
            <w>margo, -inis</w>
            <gloss><q>край</q> (например ткани)</gloss></mentioned>. По значению осетинское слово
          всего ближе к латинскому, как это имеет место и в некоторых других случаях, — см. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_amonyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_myg"/>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Probably from <w type="rec">mærz-k</w> with loss of <c>r</c>, as in <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_baz"><w>baz</w> from <w type="rec">barz</w>
            <gloss><q>pillow</q></gloss></ref>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tas"/> from <w
            type="rec">tars</w>
          <gloss><q>fear</q></gloss> etc. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
            <w>marz</w>
            <gloss><q>limit</q></gloss>, <gloss><q>border</q></gloss></mentioned>,
              <mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="got"><lang/>
              <w>marka</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
              <w>Mark</w></mentioned>
            <gloss><q>border</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
            <w>margo, -inis</w>
            <gloss><q>edge</q>, <q>margin</q> (e.g. of fabric)</gloss></mentioned>. In meaning, the
          Ossetic word is closest to the Latin, which is also seen in some other cases: see <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_amonyn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_myg"/>.</etym>
      </entry>
